.Dd March 26, 2026
.Dt GREP 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm grep
.Nd file pattern searcher
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl EFGHILRVcilnoqrvw
.Op Fl A Ar num
.Op Fl B Ar num
.Op Fl C Ar num
.Op Fl D Ar action
.Op Fl e Ar pattern
.Op Fl f Ar file
.Op Ar pattern
.Op Ar
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility searches any given input files, selecting lines that match one or
more patterns.
By default,
.Nm
prints the matching lines.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Fl A Ar num
Print
.Ar num
lines of trailing context after each match.
.It Fl B Ar num
Print
.Ar num
lines of leading context before each match.
.It Fl C Ar num
Print
.Ar num
lines of leading and trailing context surrounding each match.
.It Fl E , Fl -extended-regexp
Interpret
.Ar pattern
as an extended regular expression.
.It Fl F , Fl -fixed-strings
Interpret
.Ar pattern
as a set of fixed strings.
.It Fl G , Fl -basic-regexp
Interpret
.Ar pattern
as a basic regular expression.
This is the default.
.It Fl H
Always print filename headers with output lines.
.It Fl I
Ignore binary files.
.It Fl L , Fl -files-without-match
Print only the names of files not containing selected lines.
.It Fl R , Fl r , Fl -recursive
Recursively search subdirectories listed.
.It Fl V , Fl -version
Display version information and exit.
.It Fl c , Fl -count
Only a count of selected lines is written to standard output.
.It Fl e Ar pattern
Specify a pattern used during the search of the input.
.It Fl i , Fl -ignore-case
Perform case insensitive matching.
.It Fl l , Fl -files-with-matches
Print only the names of files containing selected lines.
.It Fl n , Fl -line-number
Precede each output line with its relative line number in the file.
.It Fl o , Fl -only-matching
Print only the matching part of the lines.
.It Fl q , Fl -quiet
Quiet mode.
Do not write anything to standard output.
Exit immediately with zero status if any match is found.
.It Fl v , Fl -invert-match
Selected lines are those not matching any of the specified patterns.
.It Fl w , Fl -word-regexp
The expression is searched for as a word.
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Sh EXAMPLES
Search for a pattern in a file:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
grep 'error' /var/log/syslog
.Ed
.Pp
Recursively search for a pattern, case insensitive:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
grep -ri 'todo' src/
.Ed
.Pp
Show 3 lines of context around each match:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
grep -C 3 'panic' *.go
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr awk 1 ,
.Xr sed 1
